# gitleaks ignore — audit L14 (2026-05-24).
#
# Reasoning: the 2026-05-24 self-pentest ran `gitleaks detect` and surfaced
# 22 hits, every one a false positive (marketing demo with a *fake* ghp_…
# token, security/page.tsx illustrative text, test fixtures, redaction-test
# inputs). Without this file the next real leak would get lost in the noise.
#
# Format: one fingerprint per line (path:rule-id:line) OR a path glob.
# Lines starting with `#` are comments. See:
#   https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks#gitleaksignore
#
# Companion durable config is in .gitleaks.toml — that's where allowlist
# paths live. This file is for case-by-case fingerprints we'd like to keep
# visible to anyone running gitleaks ad-hoc.

